// @check
// @error-at 7:7 Type `D` refers to itself; opaque/recursive type aliases are not yet supported
// Regression: a directly self-cyclic alias `type D = D` keeps its existing,
// single clean "refers to itself" error. The new never-value diagnostic is
// scoped to a `never` produced by a CONCRETE empty intersection (tagged), so it
// does NOT fire a second, duplicate error on the self-cycle's bare `never`.
type D = D
let d: D = 0
